{"article_id":"4sPWu1g73AeLY1NS","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"When the United States Supreme Court hears arguments Tuesday morning about Proposition 8 , the California ballot initiative","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"that banned gay marriage in the state ,","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"legal experts will analyze every comment and gesture","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"to learn what the justices think of the law .","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"In California , by contrast , what residents think of the law is hardly mystery .","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"Little more than four years after Californians approved the ban ,","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"their attitudes toward gay marriage have shifted dramatically .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"In 2008 , the inititiave passed with 52 percent of the vote .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"Today , some 61 percent of California voters approve of allowing same-sex couples to marry","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"- with only 32 percent opposed .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"In many ways , the forces","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"reshaping Californians ' opinions of gay marriage","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"are the same as those","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that have driven similar shifts in states nationwide .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"As homosexuality becomes more accepted and open ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"more people report having gay friends or family ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"which has removed many former objections .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"But activists say","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Prop . 8 itself created a backlash","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"that only accelerated Californians ' willingness","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"to take a fresh look at gay rights .","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"And Hollywood , California ' s most famous industry , has taken a leading role","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"in breaking down stereotypes and fears .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"\" We are all simply more comfortable with gays in our midst , \"","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"says Barbara O ' Connor , director emeritus of the Institute for Study of Politics and Media at California State University , Sacramento .","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"\" Everyone has a gay friend","depth":14},{"id":26,"text":"or their children do ,","depth":14},{"id":27,"text":"and so this fear","depth":15},{"id":28,"text":"that they are just awful","depth":15},{"id":29,"text":"has been allayed .","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"And therein lies the change . \"","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"Research from Williams Institute states","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"that there are approximately 581,300 same-sex couples in the United States ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"including 50,000 to 80,000 legally married same-sex spouses and another 85,000","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"who are in civil unions or registered domestic partnerships .","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"Approximately 20 percent of same-sex couples are raising nearly 250,000 children .","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"With that broader context , California has felt the issue acutely ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"in large part because of the controversy","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"surrounding Prop . 8 .","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"Jane Wishon ,","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"who has been married to her husband for 37 years","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"and who has three kids ,","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"says","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"her own experience points to California ' s broader post-Prop . 8 transformation .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"An elder in the Presbyterian church , she says","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"she grew up with the solid conviction","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"that marriage was simply between a man and a woman .","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"Her husband suggested to her","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"that \" separate but equal is never really equal , \"","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"but","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"while she had no animus toward gays ,","depth":15},{"id":51,"text":"she felt unbudgeable on the issue :","depth":16},{"id":52,"text":"\" Like red is just red . \"","depth":16},{"id":53,"text":"Then she stood near the signature gatherers for Prop . 8 .","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"She was only trying to help","depth":16},{"id":55,"text":"- explaining to people the complicated fact","depth":17},{"id":56,"text":"that a \" yes \" for Prop . 8 meant \" no \" to gay marriage","depth":18},{"id":57,"text":"and that a \" no \" meant \" yes \" to gay marriage .","depth":18},{"id":58,"text":"But some people had thought","depth":17},{"id":59,"text":"she was a gay-rights activist .","depth":17},{"id":60,"text":"\" They just treated me differently , \"","depth":18},{"id":61,"text":"she says .","depth":18},{"id":62,"text":"Many kept a conspicuous distance .","depth":17},{"id":63,"text":"\" I realized what LGBT","depth":17},{"id":64,"text":"[ lesbian , gay , bisexual , and transgender ]","depth":17},{"id":65,"text":"people put up with day after day ,","depth":16},{"id":66,"text":"and that cemented my support for equality , \"","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"she says .","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"Later ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"getting involved with a marriage-equality group ,","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"she met many gays","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"who wanted to get married .","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"\" I realized","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"here was a whole group of people","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"who simply loved others","depth":16},{"id":75,"text":"and wanted to spend their lives together","depth":16},{"id":76,"text":"but were never shown the respect and dignity","depth":16},{"id":77,"text":"that comes with marriage , \"","depth":16},{"id":78,"text":"she says .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"She doesn ' t want to tell others what to think ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"but suggests","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"that the American government is not living up to its promise of \" all men are created equal . \"","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"Ironically , Prop . 8 helped the gay-rights cause in California ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"activists say .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"\" Prop . 8 really activated the gay community in the state , \"","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"says Michael McKeon of Love , Honor , Cherish , a group","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"that formed in Los Angeles","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"to fight for marriage equality in 2008 .","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"\" Nobody really thought","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"it would pass ,","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"but","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"when it did ,","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"I realized","depth":15},{"id":93,"text":"I had to do something ,","depth":16},{"id":94,"text":"and get involved , \"","depth":16},{"id":95,"text":"he says .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"Dozens of teams began a focused , door-knocking campaign ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"with he and his partner of 15 years spending many hours","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"talking to people","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"and explaining the issues .","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"\" We introduced ourselves ,","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"talked about who we were","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"and why the stakes were so important , \"","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"he says .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"\" We had thousands of conversations ...","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"and we changed people 's minds . \"","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"At the same time , gay rights has become more mainstream ,","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"with President Obama last year becoming the first president","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"to announce his support for gay marriage while in office .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"High-profile California companies such as Google , Apple , and Facebook are among nearly 300 companies","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"that filed a brief in support of the challenge to the federal Defense of Marriage Act ,","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"which allows only heterosexual couples to be eligible for federal marriage benefits .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"\" Companies should care about repealing DOMA","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"because DOMA forces companies to live in the past , \"","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"says Joe Solmenese , co-founder at the law firm Gavin/Solmonese .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"you care about","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":6},{"id":120,"text":"Hollywood has also played a role","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"in reflecting this shift in attitudes ,","depth":6},{"id":122,"text":"says Robert Thompson , founder of the Bleier Center for Television and Popular Culture at Syracuse University in New York .","depth":5},{"id":123,"text":"While Ellen DeGeneres ' s coming out on \" Ellen \" was seen as a watershed moment for gays on television ,","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"more recent portrayals","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"- such as \" Will and Grace \" and \" Modern Family \" -","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"have knit gay characters more seamlessly into everyday American life .","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"\" Pop culture is not so good at pushing the envelope","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"as it is in licking it , \"","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"says Mr. Thompson .","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"Everyone knew gay people in the 1950s ,","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"but just didn ' t know","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"they were gay ,","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"he says .","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"\" Now we do . ''","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":269,"left":138,"right":268,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":138,"left":136,"right":137,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":136,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elabor